<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Fire Characteristics</h4>
	<div class="text">Historically, fire did not affect open stands. However, <i>Bromus tectorum </i>and other non-native annual grasses have invaded sites with <i>Atriplex confertifolia, </i>and these grasses readily carry fire through many stands. <i>A. confertifolia </i>is fire intolerant and does not readily recover from fire, except for establishment through seed. Slow post-fire recovery of <i>A. confertifolia </i>allows for easy invasion and subsequent replacement by <i>B. tectorum </i>(Simonin 2001a).</div>
	<table class="zebraStripe">
		
		<tr>
			<td class="key">Fire return interval</td>
			<td>Long
				
